    <descript>
      <abstract>This data layer contains rivers and ponds that occur in Newton. Boston Edison (now known as NSTAR) provided the original version of this data layer. Some editing was done based on the 2000 Orthophotography by the GIS Administrator.</abstract>
      <purpose>This layer is intended for researchers, students, and policy makers for reference and mapping purposes, and may be used for basic applications such as viewing, querying, and map output production. This layer will provide a basemap for layers related to hydrology, environmental management, urban planning or to support graphical overlays and analysis with other spatial data. 
More advanced user applications may focus on urban planning and policies, public works, or utilities purposes, including defining boundaries, managing assets and facilities, integrating attribute databases with geographic features, spatial analysis, and presentation output.</purpose>
    </descript>
